<h2 class="bac"><img class="pclose" src="../images/clear.gif" alt="Hide information" title="Hide information">Our Business</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac">Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America&#39;s commitment to the mortgage industry is focused on continuous growth, increased teamwork, and excellent customer service. As the nation&#39;s largest mortgage lender and loan servicer, and the world&#39;s most trusted lender, Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America Home Loans embraces a commitment to responsible home lending. Our every action is focused on Bringing Opportunity Home for those we serve, assisting new and existing customers in achieving their dreams of home ownership and preservation.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif" alt="Show information" title="Show information">Overview</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac">Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America is investing in high-caliber talent to expand the bank&#39;s cadre of leaders. The program seeks to develop leaders with knowledge and skills of the mortgage business at Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America by creating opportunities to learn multiple disciplines through rotations that build upon one another. The program will also strengthen leadership skills and attributes that are applicable across the corporation.</p>
<p class="bac nobr">The program includes:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Two-year Rotational program in Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America Home Loans and Legacy Asset Services.</li>
	<li>Participants rotate through three areas of the bank&#39;s critical mortgage business over 24 months to build breadth and depth in Credit and Risk Policy. Rotations may exist in the following areas and are selected based on a combination of business need and participant interest:</li>
	<li>Credit, Product and Pricing</li>
	<li>Business Operations</li>
	<li>Underwriting and Fulfillment</li>
	<li>Secondary Marketing</li>
	<li>Credit Loss Mitigation Strategies &amp; Governance</li>
	<li>Customer Experience  &amp; Mortgage Operations</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">Associates are developed for future leadership responsibilities with one of the country&#39;s largest mortgage businesses - and one of the world&#39;s largest banks - during a period of industry transformation.</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Participation in Program developmental opportunities such as executive Leader exposure, Monthly Connect meetings with program peers, as well as performance and leadership coaching from Program Management throughout the 24 month period.</li>
	<li>Rotation examples could include: Strategy Consultant, Pricing Analyst, Risk Manager, Business Analyst</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif" alt="Show information" title="Show information">Qualifications</h2>
<div>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>MBA in Strategic Management, Accounting, Finance, Business Administration, Economics or related discipline</li>
	<li>Exceptional communication skills (both written and verbal)</li>
	<li>Demonstrated leadership, initiative, and resourcefulness in school, community, and/or work experience</li>
	<li>Strong work ethic, ability to multi-task, and teamwork orientation</li>
	<li>Dedicated to building a career in financial services</li>
	<li>Minimum GPA of 3.0</li>
	<li>Must have eligibility to work in the US</li>
	<li>Geographic mobility/flexibility</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif" alt="Show information" title="Show information">Training</h2>
