<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif" alt="Show information" title="Show information"><span style="color: #D40019;">Rotation Example #1:</span> Origination Credit Policy</h2>
<div>
<h3 class="bac">Group Description</h3>
<p class="bac nobr">Origination Credit Policy, an integral part of the Credit Origination Strategies group, helps fulfill the corporate mission of managing credit risk while offering world-class first mortgage products that benefit both the customer and Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America. Origination Credit Policy team members are loan program and policy experts in first mortgage credit policy. The organization is responsible for the following:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Ongoing development and policy change management of enterprise-wide credit origination policies and credit risk strategies for GSE standard and negotiated programs; GSE Affordable programs; Mortgage Insurance; FHA policy; VA policy; Mortgage Insurance policy and vendors; Non-conforming mortgage programs and policy; Balance Sheet mortgage programs and policies; and Automated Underwriting Systems;</li>
	<li>Assess the impact of policy and product changes, then implement policy change using the Product Change process;</li>
	<li>Alignment and ongoing management of credit policy for the Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac master agreements;</li>
	<li>Policy oversight, including cross reporting on product performance, quality-control results, and repurchase volume;</li>
	<li>Ongoing assessment and improvement of mortgage loan manufacturing quality; and</li>
	<li>Provide information support as credit policy subject-matter experts to all levels of Bank management.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="bac">Responsibilities:</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>The candidate would assist in two capacities for two teams: (1) Investor Relations and Governance, and (2) Loan Quality Initiative.</li>
	<li>Leverage Six Sigma knowledge tools to recommend innovative solutions for information management and workflow.</li>
	<li>Create and implement practices and processes that will drive accountability to comply with governance policies.</li>
	<li>Compile audit results and create analytical summaries (root cause analysis and performance trends).</li>
	<li>Operational responsibilities include the following:</li>
	<li>Research available databases and determine which best suits the needs of the department or assist in writing a project charter and BRD to create new database.</li>
	<li>Evaluate current monthly reporting and recommend improvement. Train co-workers on using PowerPoint to create more effective reports.</li>
	<li>Assist with governance activity by auditing PCs to ensure they were completed as per policy.</li>
	<li>Assist with LQI projects: summarize data input in report format, such as Excel, tracking and reporting on status of loan audits.</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif" alt="Show information" title="Show information"><span style="color: #D40019;">Rotation Example #2:</span> Loss Forecasting</h2>
<div>
<h3 class="bac">Group Description</h3>
<p class="bac">Loss Forecasting is responsible for estimating future net credit losses of the First Mortgage Held for Investment Portfolio. The Loss Forecast is used to estimate Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America&#39;s Allowance for Loan, Lease Losses. The department is also responsible for projecting future net credit losses under the Enterprise Stress Test. Loss Forecasting leverages financial models to estimate future net credit losses.</p>
<p class="bac">Loss Forecasting also engages directly with the Servicing Department to estimate the financial benefits of Home Retention Strategies</p>
<h3 class="bac">Responsibilities:</h3>
<p class="bac nobr">The MBA intern will be responsible for:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Performing complex analysis and modeling that maximizes profits and asset growth and minimizes credit and operating losses and other risk exposures</li>
	<li>Reviewing and analyzing trends in current population distributions and recommends strategies</li>
	<li>Developing more complex program models to extract data and use databases to provide statistical and financial modeling</li>
	<li>Participating in the rollout of company-wide pilot programs developed as a result of programmed models</li>
	<li>Analyzing portfolio trends, concerning credit score cutoffs, loss trends, portfolio dynamics, and bureau scoring criteria</li>
	<li>Problem solving, conceptual thinking quantitative and analytical skills</li>
	<li>Influencing senior leaders with mortgage backgrounds on strategic initiatives  &amp; improvements</li>
	<li>Developing knowledge of mortgage market trends (e.g., competitive landscape, products, secondary markets, sales channels  &amp; fulfillment)</li>
	<li>Independently managing work streams from scoping to completion</li>
	<li>Driving development  &amp; implementation of Loss Mitigation program for applicable segments</li>
	<li>Providing strategic and &#39;on the ground&#39; support to Servicing partners</li>
	<li>Building out and remaining expert in policies / practices for end-to-end retention activities</li>
	<li>Coordinating the production of performance reports for senior management</li>
	<li>Providing analytical support on various product strategies to ensure company goals are met</li>
	<li>Building effective presentations for both verbal  &amp; written communications</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

